    hasGaps: true,
    published: false,
    body: "The body kept the scar.\n\nThe rest of me forgot, some days. The body did not. The body was there and stayed there, on the table, under the lights that are not stage lights. It remembers what I would move past. It does not ask me first.\n\nThere is a scar. `[[NEEDS: location and appearance of the surgical scar]]` I find it without looking. My fingers know the way. The hair grows over it and you would not see it, but my fingers go there the way the tongue goes to a broken tooth. Not to fix it. To check that it is still where it was.\n\nThe eye is the thing people would notice if they watched long enough. One of them does not track right. `[[NEEDS: which eye, and the specific way it lags or drifts]]` Most of the time it follows the other one the way a tired horse follows the lead horse. Close enough. Half a step behind. When I am rested it is nearly nothing. When I am not, it falls back, and what it sends up does not line up with what the good eye sends up. Then I get two of everything.\n\nThat is the double vision. I have written around it for a long time. The two images. The world seen twice. I made it sound like a thing I chose. It is not a thing I chose. It is the eye. The eye does not track because of what they went in after. I will not say more about it than that.\n\nThe hand is quieter. `[[NEEDS: which hand, and the specific deficit — strength, fine motor, sensation, tremor]]` It works. It does what I tell it. But there is a delay in the telling now, a small customs house the order passes through, and on the far side the hand does the thing a beat after I asked. With a deck of cards you would not catch it. I have done the moves so many thousands of times that they live below the part that got damaged. The hands kept the deck the way the body kept the scar. That is the one mercy in it. The oldest thing I knew was the thing it could not reach.\n\nThe new things are harder than the old things. A man buttons a shirt without thinking. He thinks about his coffee, or the thing he said last night that he should not have said, and the buttons happen below all that. I think about the buttons. I think about the small ones at the cuff. I think about the key going into the lock, the turn of it, the lift of the cup so it does not spill. None of these are hard. All of them are deliberate. I have to be there for them. I cannot send the body ahead and follow with my mind.\n\nSo I am slow in a way that does not show. I leave earlier. I do the careful things in the morning, when the eye is rested and the hand answers quickest, and I leave the rest of the day for the things that forgive a delay. Talking forgives a delay. Cards forgive it. Stairs in the dark do not. A knife does not. I plan around the things that do not forgive.\n\nPeople tell me I seem calm. Steady, they say. They mean it as a thing I am. It is not a thing I am. It is a thing I do, one motion at a time, because the other choice is to knock the cup. The calm is the slowness in a clean shirt.\n\nThere is a cost to being there for everything. It tires me in a way I cannot explain to a man who buttons his cuffs and thinks of his coffee. He spends nothing. I spend something on each thing, all day, small coins, and by dark I am out of them and not done. That is part of why the body will not power down. It has been counting coins since morning and it does not know how to stop.\n\nI do not hate the body for keeping the scar. It was the body that took me to the other side. It went in and came out and kept going. The eye that does not track is the eye I still see with. The hand that answers late still holds the deck. I ask more of them than I used to, in smaller amounts, more careful, and they give it.\n\nSome mornings I stand at the sink and look in the glass and there is one of me, the two images stacked square. Some mornings there are two, half a step apart, asking to be put back together. I have stopped waiting for the morning when there is always one. The buttons get done either way. We leave earlier. We are not in a hurry.",
